{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01BeigRkuyQfPaoLFxTYR8ZU","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package config\n     2→\n     3→import (\n     4→\t\"os\"\n     5→\t\"strconv\"\n     6→)\n     7→\n     8→type Config struct {\n     9→\tPort        string\n    10→\tDBPath      string\n    11→\tWorkerCount int\n    12→}\n    13→\n    14→func Load() Config {\n    15→\tc := Config{\n    16→\t\tPort:        \"8080\",\n    17→\t\tDBPath:      \"./miniflow.db\",\n    18→\t\tWorkerCount: 4,\n    19→\t}\n    20→\tif v := os.Getenv(\"PORT\"); v != \"\" {\n    21→\t\tc.Port = v\n    22→\t}\n    23→\tif v := os.Getenv(\"DB_PATH\"); v != \"\" {\n    24→\t\tc.DBPath = v\n    25→\t}\n    26→\tif v := os.Getenv(\"WORKER_COUNT\"); v != \"\" {\n    27→\t\tif n, err := strconv.Atoi(v); err == nil && n > 0 {\n    28→\t\t\tc.WorkerCount = n\n    29→\t\t}\n    30→\t}\n    31→\treturn c\n    32→}\n    33→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_017DaC9TpQABNBwJVFEELshq","session_id":"701e3a6a-36af-4762-8d76-051700988d74","uuid":"0bba17bf-15db-4d4d-8105-541c25794bca"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_017DaC9TpQABNBwJVFEELshq","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Here is a thorough breakdown of the entire miniflow codebase.\n\n---\n\n## Project Structure\n\n```\nminiflow/\n├── cmd/\n│   ├── server/main.go          # Server entrypoint\n│   └── cli/main.go             # CLI entrypoint\n├── internal/\n│   ├── config/config.go        # Config loading (env vars)\n│   ├── model/\n│   │   ├── workflow.go         # Workflow + ActivitySpec types\n│   │   ├── run.go              # WorkflowRun + ActivityRun types\n│   │   └── event.go            # Event type + event constants\n│   ├── store/\n│   │   ├── store.go            # SQLite persistence (Store struct)\n│   │   └── errors.go           # Sentinel errors\n│   ├── handler/\n│   │   ├── handler.go          # HTTP handler + route registration\n│   │   └── types.go            # Request/response DTOs\n│   ├── client/\n│   │   └── client.go           # HTTP client library (mirrors server types)\n│   ├── activity/\n│   │   ├── registry.go         # HandlerFunc type + Registry\n│   │   ├── worker.go           # WorkerPool (polls + executes activities)\n│   │   └── builtin.go          # 5 built-in activity handlers\n│   └── executor/\n│       ├── executor.go         # Executor (workflow state machine)\n│       └── scheduler.go        # Scheduler (periodic polling loop)\n├── go.mod\n└── go.sum\n```\n\n---\n\n## 1. go.mod\n\n**Module:** `miniflow`  \n**Go version:** 1.25.1  \n**Direct dependencies:**\n- `github.com/go-chi/chi/v5 v5.2.5` - HTTP router\n- `github.com/google/uuid v1.6.0` - UUID generation\n- `modernc.org/sqlite v1.46.1` - Pure-Go SQLite driver (CGo-free)\n\n---\n\n## 2. Key Types: `internal/model`\n\n### `model/workflow.go`\n\n```go\ntype ActivitySpec struct {\n    Name           string `json:\"name\"`\n    Type           string `json:\"type\"`\n    InputExpr      string `json:\"input_expr\"`\n    TimeoutSeconds int    `json:\"timeout_seconds\"`\n    MaxRetries     int    `json:\"max_retries\"`\n}\n\ntype WorkflowDefinition struct {\n    Activities []ActivitySpec `json:\"activities\"`\n}\n\ntype Workflow struct {\n    ID         string             `json:\"id\"`\n    Name       string             `json:\"name\"`\n    Definition WorkflowDefinition `json:\"definition\"`\n    CreatedAt  time.Time          `json:\"created_at\"`\n}\n```\n\n### `model/run.go`\n\nStatus constants: `pending`, `running`, `completed`, `failed`, `cancelled`\n\n```go\ntype WorkflowRun struct {\n    ID          string     `json:\"id\"`\n    WorkflowID  string     `json:\"workflow_id\"`\n    Status      string     `json:\"status\"`\n    Input       string     `json:\"input\"`\n    Output      string     `json:\"output\"`\n    CurrentStep int        `json:\"current_step\"`\n    StartedAt   *time.Time `json:\"started_at,omitempty\"`\n    CompletedAt *time.Time `json:\"completed_at,omitempty\"`\n    CreatedAt   time.Time  `json:\"created_at\"`\n}\n\ntype ActivityRun struct {\n    ID             string     `json:\"id\"`\n    WorkflowRunID  string     `json:\"workflow_run_id\"`\n    ActivityName   string     `json:\"activity_name\"`\n    StepIndex      int        `json:\"step_index\"`\n    Status         string     `json:\"status\"`\n    Input          string     `json:\"input\"`\n    Output         string     `json:\"output\"`\n    Attempts       int        `json:\"attempts\"`\n    MaxRetries     int        `json:\"max_retries\"`\n    TimeoutSeconds int        `json:\"timeout_seconds\"`\n    StartedAt      *time.Time `json:\"started_at,omitempty\"`\n    CompletedAt    *time.Time `json:\"completed_at,omitempty\"`\n    LastHeartbeat  *time.Time `json:\"last_heartbeat,omitempty\"`\n    CreatedAt      time.Time  `json:\"created_at\"`\n}\n```\n\n### `model/event.go`\n\nEvent type constants:\n- Workflow-level: `workflow_started`, `workflow_completed`, `workflow_failed`, `workflow_cancelled`\n- Activity-level: `activity_scheduled`, `activity_started`, `activity_completed`, `activity_failed`, `activity_retried`, `activity_timed_out`, `activity_heartbeat`\n\n```go\ntype Event struct {\n    ID            int64     `json:\"id\"`\n    WorkflowRunID string    `json:\"workflow_run_id\"`\n    ActivityRunID string    `json:\"activity_run_id,omitempty\"`\n    EventType     string    `json:\"event_type\"`\n    Payload       string    `json:\"payload\"`\n    CreatedAt     time.Time `json:\"created_at\"`\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## 3. Store: `internal/store`\n\n### `store.Store` struct\nBacked by a SQLite database (WAL mode, foreign keys on). Holds a `*sql.DB` and a `sync.Mutex` for serializing `ClaimNextActivity`.\n\n### Schema\n4 tables: `workflows`, `workflow_runs`, `activity_runs`, `events`\n\n### Public methods\n\n| Method | Signature |\n|---|---|\n| `NewStore` | `func NewStore(dsn string) (*Store, error)` |\n| `Close` | `func (s *Store) Close() error` |\n| `CreateWorkflow` | `func (s *Store) CreateWorkflow(w *model.Workflow) error` |\n| `GetWorkflow` | `func (s *Store) GetWorkflow(id string) (*model.Workflow, error)` |\n| `GetWorkflowByName` | `func (s *Store) GetWorkflowByName(name string) (*model.Workflow, error)` |\n| `ListWorkflows` | `func (s *Store) ListWorkflows() ([]model.Workflow, error)` |\n| `CreateRun` | `func (s *Store) CreateRun(r *model.WorkflowRun) error` |\n| `GetRun` | `func (s *Store) GetRun(id string) (*model.WorkflowRun, error)` |\n| `ListRuns` | `func (s *Store) ListRuns(status string, limit int) ([]model.WorkflowRun, error)` |\n| `UpdateRun` | `func (s *Store) UpdateRun(r *model.WorkflowRun) error` |\n| `CreateActivityRun` | `func (s *Store) CreateActivityRun(ar *model.ActivityRun) error` |\n| `GetActivityRun` | `func (s *Store) GetActivityRun(id string) (*model.ActivityRun, error)` |\n| `GetActivityRunsByRunID` | `func (s *Store) GetActivityRunsByRunID(runID string) ([]model.ActivityRun, error)` |\n| `UpdateActivityRun` | `func (s *Store) UpdateActivityRun(ar *model.ActivityRun) error` |\n| `ClaimNextActivity` | `func (s *Store) ClaimNextActivity() (*model.ActivityRun, error)` |\n| `AppendEvent` | `func (s *Store) AppendEvent(e *model.Event) error` |\n| `ListEvents` | `func (s *Store) ListEvents(runID string) ([]model.Event, error)` |\n| `Stats` | `func (s *Store) Stats() (map[string]int, error)` |\n\n`ClaimNextActivity` is the key atomic operation: within a mutex-protected transaction, it finds the oldest `pending` activity run and atomically marks it `running` with `started_at = now`.\n\n### Sentinel errors\n- `store.ErrNotFound`\n- `store.ErrDuplicateWorkflow`\n\n---\n\n## 4. Handler: `internal/handler`\n\n### Route Registration (`handler.New`)\n\n```go\nfunc New(s *store.Store, ex *executor.Executor) http.Handler\n```\n\nAll routes registered on a `chi.Router`:\n\n| Method | Path | Handler | Description |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| `POST` | `/api/workflows` | `CreateWorkflow` | Register a new workflow |\n| `GET` | `/api/workflows` | `ListWorkflows` | List all workflows |\n| `GET` | `/api/workflows/{name}` | `GetWorkflow` | Get workflow by name |\n| `POST` | `/api/workflows/{name}/run` | `StartRun` | Start a new run |\n| `GET` | `/api/runs` | `ListRuns` | List runs (`?status=`, `?limit=`) |\n| `GET` | `/api/runs/{id}` | `GetRun` | Get run + activities detail |\n| `GET` | `/api/runs/{id}/events` | `ListEvents` | Get event timeline |\n| `POST` | `/api/runs/{id}/cancel` | `CancelRun` | Cancel a run |\n| `GET` | `/api/stats` | `Stats` | Run counts by status |\n| `GET` | `/health` | `Health` | Health check |\n\n### Request/Response DTOs (`handler/types.go`)\n\n```go\ntype CreateWorkflowRequest struct {\n    Name       string                   `json:\"name\"`\n    Definition model.WorkflowDefinition `json:\"definition\"`\n}\n\ntype StartRunRequest struct {\n    Input string `json:\"input\"`\n}\n\ntype RunDetailResponse struct {\n    model.WorkflowRun\n    Activities []model.ActivityRun `json:\"activities\"`\n}\n\ntype StatsResponse struct {\n    Counts map[string]int `json:\"counts\"`\n}\n\ntype ErrorResponse struct {\n    Error string `json:\"error\"`\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## 5. Client Library: `internal/client`\n\n### `client.Client`\n\n```go\nfunc NewClient(baseURL string) *Client\n// Default baseURL: http://localhost:8080, HTTP timeout: 30s\n```\n\n### All Public Methods\n\n```go\nfunc (c *Client) RegisterWorkflow(name string, definition WorkflowDefinition) (*Workflow, error)\nfunc (c *Client) GetWorkflow(name string) (*Workflow, error)\nfunc (c *Client) ListWorkflows() ([]Workflow, error)\nfunc (c *Client) StartRun(workflowName string, input string) (*WorkflowRun, error)\nfunc (c *Client) GetRun(id string) (*RunDetailResponse, error)\nfunc (c *Client) ListRuns(status string, limit int) ([]WorkflowRun, error)\nfunc (c *Client) GetEvents(runID string) ([]Event, error)\nfunc (c *Client) CancelRun(id string) error\nfunc (c *Client) Stats() (*StatsResponse, error)\nfunc (c *Client) Health() error\n```\n\nNon-2xx responses are returned as `*APIError{StatusCode int, Message string}`. The client mirrors all server model types locally (`Workflow`, `WorkflowRun`, `ActivityRun`, `Event`, `RunDetailResponse`, `StatsResponse`).\n\n---\n\n## 6. Activity Package: `internal/activity`\n\n### Registry (`registry.go`)\n\n```go\ntype HandlerFunc func(ctx context.Context, input string) (string, error)\n\ntype Registry struct { ... }\n\nfunc NewRegistry() *Registry\nfunc (r *Registry) Register(name string, handler HandlerFunc)\nfunc (r *Registry) Execute(ctx context.Context, name string, input string) (string, error)\n```\n\nThread-safe via `sync.RWMutex`. Returns an error if no handler is registered for the given name.\n\n### WorkerPool (`worker.go`)\n\n```go\ntype ActivityStore interface {\n    ClaimNextActivity() (*model.ActivityRun, error)\n    UpdateActivityRun(ar *model.ActivityRun) error\n    AppendEvent(e *model.Event) error\n}\n\ntype WorkerPool struct { ... }\n\nfunc NewWorkerPool(store ActivityStore, registry *Registry, count int, interval time.Duration) *WorkerPool\nfunc (wp *WorkerPool) Start()   // launches `count` goroutines\nfunc (wp *WorkerPool) Stop()    // signals quit, waits for goroutines\n```\n\nEach worker goroutine in `workerLoop` continuously calls `ClaimNextActivity`, then `executeActivity`. On each execution:\n1. Marks activity `running`, emits `activity_started`\n2. Launches a heartbeat goroutine (ticks every 5s, writes `last_heartbeat` + `activity_heartbeat` event)\n3. Calls `registry.Execute(ctx, ar.ActivityName, ar.Input)` with the configured timeout context\n4. On success: sets `completed`, emits `activity_completed`\n5. On failure with retries remaining: resets to `pending`, emits `activity_retried` or `activity_timed_out`\n6. On failure with retries exhausted: sets `failed`, emits `activity_failed` or `activity_timed_out`\n\n### Built-in Handlers (`builtin.go`)\n\nRegistered by `RegisterBuiltins(r *Registry)`:\n\n| Name | Input | Output | Description |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| `noop` | any | same as input | Pass-through |\n| `sleep` | `{\"duration_ms\": N}` | `{\"slept\": N}` | Sleep for N ms, respects context cancellation |\n| `http-call` | `{\"url\":\"...\", \"method\":\"GET\", \"body\":\"...\"}` | `{\"status\": N, \"body\":\"...\"}` | Makes an HTTP request |\n| `log` | `{\"message\": \"...\"}` | `{\"logged\": true}` | Logs a message via `log.Printf` |\n| `fail` | any | error | Always returns an error (for testing retries) |\n\n---\n\n## 7. Executor Package: `internal/executor`\n\n### `RunStore` Interface\n\n```go\ntype RunStore interface {\n    GetRun(id string) (*model.WorkflowRun, error)\n    UpdateRun(r *model.WorkflowRun) error\n    GetWorkflow(id string) (*model.Workflow, error)\n    CreateActivityRun(ar *model.ActivityRun) error\n    GetActivityRunsByRunID(runID string) ([]model.ActivityRun, error)\n    AppendEvent(e *model.Event) error\n    ListRuns(status string, limit int) ([]model.WorkflowRun, error)\n}\n```\n\n### `Executor` (`executor.go`)\n\n```go\nfunc NewExecutor(store RunStore) *Executor\nfunc (e *Executor) StartRun(runID string) error\nfunc (e *Executor) CancelRun(runID string) error\nfunc (e *Executor) AdvanceRun(runID string) error\n```\n\n`AdvanceRun` is the core state machine:\n- If `currentStep >= len(activities)`: complete the run\n- If no `ActivityRun` exists for `currentStep`: call `scheduleActivity` (creates `ActivityRun` + emits `activity_scheduled`)\n- If current activity is `completed`: increment `CurrentStep`, schedule next activity (or complete run)\n- If current activity is `failed` with retries exhausted: fail the run\n- If current activity is `pending`/`running`: do nothing (wait)\n\nInput expression resolution via `resolveInputExpr`:\n- `\"$.input\"` → workflow run's raw input\n- `\"$.steps[N].output\"` → Nth activity run's output\n- anything else (or empty) → workflow run's raw input\n\n### `Scheduler` (`scheduler.go`)\n\n```go\nfunc NewScheduler(executor *Executor, store RunStore, interval time.Duration) *Scheduler\nfunc (s *Scheduler) Start()   // background goroutine\nfunc (s *Scheduler) Stop()    // closes quit channel\n```\n\nOn every tick (`500ms` by default from `cmd/server/main.go`):\n1. Lists all `pending` runs (up to 100), calls `executor.StartRun` on each\n2. Lists all `running` runs (up to 100), calls `executor.AdvanceRun` on each\n\n---\n\n## 8. Config: `internal/config`\n\n```go\ntype Config struct {\n    Port        string   // default: \"8080\", env: PORT\n    DBPath      string   // default: \"./miniflow.db\", env: DB_PATH\n    WorkerCount int      // default: 4, env: WORKER_COUNT\n}\n\nfunc Load() Config\n```\n\n---\n\n## Server Startup Wiring (`cmd/server/main.go`)\n\n```\nconfig.Load()\n  -> store.NewStore(cfg.DBPath)\n  -> activity.NewRegistry() + RegisterBuiltins()\n  -> activity.NewWorkerPool(store, registry, cfg.WorkerCount, 500ms).Start()\n  -> executor.NewExecutor(store)\n  -> executor.NewScheduler(ex, store, 500ms).Start()\n  -> handler.New(store, ex) -> http.Server on :PORT\n  -> graceful shutdown on SIGINT/SIGTERM\n```\n\nBoth the scheduler and worker pool poll at **500ms intervals**. The scheduler drives the workflow state machine; the worker pool claims and executes individual activities. The `store.Store` satisfies both the `RunStore` and `ActivityStore` interfaces directly."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a339f6bf0a424f502 (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 51286\ntool_uses: 18\nduration_ms: 81872</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"701e3a6a-36af-4762-8d76-051700988d74","uuid":"46945a72-976c-45eb-8b9f-64487713844e","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Explore the miniflow codebase at /Users/michaelhabib/dev/teams-sbx/agent-orchestra/examples/miniflow. I need to understand:\n1. The full project structure (all files)\n2. Key types in internal/model (Workflow, WorkflowRun, ActivityRun, Event)\n3. The store interface (internal/store)\n4. The handler setup (internal/handler) - how routes are registered, what endpoints exist\n5. The client library (internal/client) - all methods and their signatures\n6. The activity package (internal/activity) - registry, worker, built-in handlers\n7. The executor package (internal/executor) - executor and scheduler\n8. go.mod contents\n\nBe thorough - read all the key files.","agentId":"a339f6bf0a424f502","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Here is a thorough breakdown of the entire miniflow codebase.\n\n---\n\n## Project Structure\n\n```\nminiflow/\n├── cmd/\n│   ├── server/main.go          # Server entrypoint\n│   └── cli/main.go             # CLI entrypoint\n├── internal/\n│   ├── config/config.go        # Config loading (env vars)\n│   ├── model/\n│   │   ├── workflow.go         # Workflow + ActivitySpec types\n│   │   ├── run.go              # WorkflowRun + ActivityRun types\n│   │   └── event.go            # Event type + event constants\n│   ├── store/\n│   │   ├── store.go            # SQLite persistence (Store struct)\n│   │   └── errors.go           # Sentinel errors\n│   ├── handler/\n│   │   ├── handler.go          # HTTP handler + route registration\n│   │   └── types.go            # Request/response DTOs\n│   ├── client/\n│   │   └── client.go           # HTTP client library (mirrors server types)\n│   ├── activity/\n│   │   ├── registry.go         # HandlerFunc type + Registry\n│   │   ├── worker.go           # WorkerPool (polls + executes activities)\n│   │   └── builtin.go          # 5 built-in activity handlers\n│   └── executor/\n│       ├── executor.go         # Executor (workflow state machine)\n│       └── scheduler.go        # Scheduler (periodic polling loop)\n├── go.mod\n└── go.sum\n```\n\n---\n\n## 1. go.mod\n\n**Module:** `miniflow`  \n**Go version:** 1.25.1  \n**Direct dependencies:**\n- `github.com/go-chi/chi/v5 v5.2.5` - HTTP router\n- `github.com/google/uuid v1.6.0` - UUID generation\n- `modernc.org/sqlite v1.46.1` - Pure-Go SQLite driver (CGo-free)\n\n---\n\n## 2. Key Types: `internal/model`\n\n### `model/workflow.go`\n\n```go\ntype ActivitySpec struct {\n    Name           string `json:\"name\"`\n    Type           string `json:\"type\"`\n    InputExpr      string `json:\"input_expr\"`\n    TimeoutSeconds int    `json:\"timeout_seconds\"`\n    MaxRetries     int    `json:\"max_retries\"`\n}\n\ntype WorkflowDefinition struct {\n    Activities []ActivitySpec `json:\"activities\"`\n}\n\ntype Workflow struct {\n    ID         string             `json:\"id\"`\n    Name       string             `json:\"name\"`\n    Definition WorkflowDefinition `json:\"definition\"`\n    CreatedAt  time.Time          `json:\"created_at\"`\n}\n```\n\n### `model/run.go`\n\nStatus constants: `pending`, `running`, `completed`, `failed`, `cancelled`\n\n```go\ntype WorkflowRun struct {\n    ID          string     `json:\"id\"`\n    WorkflowID  string     `json:\"workflow_id\"`\n    Status      string     `json:\"status\"`\n    Input       string     `json:\"input\"`\n    Output      string     `json:\"output\"`\n    CurrentStep int        `json:\"current_step\"`\n    StartedAt   *time.Time `json:\"started_at,omitempty\"`\n    CompletedAt *time.Time `json:\"completed_at,omitempty\"`\n    CreatedAt   time.Time  `json:\"created_at\"`\n}\n\ntype ActivityRun struct {\n    ID             string     `json:\"id\"`\n    WorkflowRunID  string     `json:\"workflow_run_id\"`\n    ActivityName   string     `json:\"activity_name\"`\n    StepIndex      int        `json:\"step_index\"`\n    Status         string     `json:\"status\"`\n    Input          string     `json:\"input\"`\n    Output         string     `json:\"output\"`\n    Attempts       int        `json:\"attempts\"`\n    MaxRetries     int        `json:\"max_retries\"`\n    TimeoutSeconds int        `json:\"timeout_seconds\"`\n    StartedAt      *time.Time `json:\"started_at,omitempty\"`\n    CompletedAt    *time.Time `json:\"completed_at,omitempty\"`\n    LastHeartbeat  *time.Time `json:\"last_heartbeat,omitempty\"`\n    CreatedAt      time.Time  `json:\"created_at\"`\n}\n```\n\n### `model/event.go`\n\nEvent type constants:\n- Workflow-level: `workflow_started`, `workflow_completed`, `workflow_failed`, `workflow_cancelled`\n- Activity-level: `activity_scheduled`, `activity_started`, `activity_completed`, `activity_failed`, `activity_retried`, `activity_timed_out`, `activity_heartbeat`\n\n```go\ntype Event struct {\n    ID            int64     `json:\"id\"`\n    WorkflowRunID string    `json:\"workflow_run_id\"`\n    ActivityRunID string    `json:\"activity_run_id,omitempty\"`\n    EventType     string    `json:\"event_type\"`\n    Payload       string    `json:\"payload\"`\n    CreatedAt     time.Time `json:\"created_at\"`\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## 3. Store: `internal/store`\n\n### `store.Store` struct\nBacked by a SQLite database (WAL mode, foreign keys on). Holds a `*sql.DB` and a `sync.Mutex` for serializing `ClaimNextActivity`.\n\n### Schema\n4 tables: `workflows`, `workflow_runs`, `activity_runs`, `events`\n\n### Public methods\n\n| Method | Signature |\n|---|---|\n| `NewStore` | `func NewStore(dsn string) (*Store, error)` |\n| `Close` | `func (s *Store) Close() error` |\n| `CreateWorkflow` | `func (s *Store) CreateWorkflow(w *model.Workflow) error` |\n| `GetWorkflow` | `func (s *Store) GetWorkflow(id string) (*model.Workflow, error)` |\n| `GetWorkflowByName` | `func (s *Store) GetWorkflowByName(name string) (*model.Workflow, error)` |\n| `ListWorkflows` | `func (s *Store) ListWorkflows() ([]model.Workflow, error)` |\n| `CreateRun` | `func (s *Store) CreateRun(r *model.WorkflowRun) error` |\n| `GetRun` | `func (s *Store) GetRun(id string) (*model.WorkflowRun, error)` |\n| `ListRuns` | `func (s *Store) ListRuns(status string, limit int) ([]model.WorkflowRun, error)` |\n| `UpdateRun` | `func (s *Store) UpdateRun(r *model.WorkflowRun) error` |\n| `CreateActivityRun` | `func (s *Store) CreateActivityRun(ar *model.ActivityRun) error` |\n| `GetActivityRun` | `func (s *Store) GetActivityRun(id string) (*model.ActivityRun, error)` |\n| `GetActivityRunsByRunID` | `func (s *Store) GetActivityRunsByRunID(runID string) ([]model.ActivityRun, error)` |\n| `UpdateActivityRun` | `func (s *Store) UpdateActivityRun(ar *model.ActivityRun) error` |\n| `ClaimNextActivity` | `func (s *Store) ClaimNextActivity() (*model.ActivityRun, error)` |\n| `AppendEvent` | `func (s *Store) AppendEvent(e *model.Event) error` |\n| `ListEvents` | `func (s *Store) ListEvents(runID string) ([]model.Event, error)` |\n| `Stats` | `func (s *Store) Stats() (map[string]int, error)` |\n\n`ClaimNextActivity` is the key atomic operation: within a mutex-protected transaction, it finds the oldest `pending` activity run and atomically marks it `running` with `started_at = now`.\n\n### Sentinel errors\n- `store.ErrNotFound`\n- `store.ErrDuplicateWorkflow`\n\n---\n\n## 4. Handler: `internal/handler`\n\n### Route Registration (`handler.New`)\n\n```go\nfunc New(s *store.Store, ex *executor.Executor) http.Handler\n```\n\nAll routes registered on a `chi.Router`:\n\n| Method | Path | Handler | Description |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| `POST` | `/api/workflows` | `CreateWorkflow` | Register a new workflow |\n| `GET` | `/api/workflows` | `ListWorkflows` | List all workflows |\n| `GET` | `/api/workflows/{name}` | `GetWorkflow` | Get workflow by name |\n| `POST` | `/api/workflows/{name}/run` | `StartRun` | Start a new run |\n| `GET` | `/api/runs` | `ListRuns` | List runs (`?status=`, `?limit=`) |\n| `GET` | `/api/runs/{id}` | `GetRun` | Get run + activities detail |\n| `GET` | `/api/runs/{id}/events` | `ListEvents` | Get event timeline |\n| `POST` | `/api/runs/{id}/cancel` | `CancelRun` | Cancel a run |\n| `GET` | `/api/stats` | `Stats` | Run counts by status |\n| `GET` | `/health` | `Health` | Health check |\n\n### Request/Response DTOs (`handler/types.go`)\n\n```go\ntype CreateWorkflowRequest struct {\n    Name       string                   `json:\"name\"`\n    Definition model.WorkflowDefinition `json:\"definition\"`\n}\n\ntype StartRunRequest struct {\n    Input string `json:\"input\"`\n}\n\ntype RunDetailResponse struct {\n    model.WorkflowRun\n    Activities []model.ActivityRun `json:\"activities\"`\n}\n\ntype StatsResponse struct {\n    Counts map[string]int `json:\"counts\"`\n}\n\ntype ErrorResponse struct {\n    Error string `json:\"error\"`\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## 5. Client Library: `internal/client`\n\n### `client.Client`\n\n```go\nfunc NewClient(baseURL string) *Client\n// Default baseURL: http://localhost:8080, HTTP timeout: 30s\n```\n\n### All Public Methods\n\n```go\nfunc (c *Client) RegisterWorkflow(name string, definition WorkflowDefinition) (*Workflow, error)\nfunc (c *Client) GetWorkflow(name string) (*Workflow, error)\nfunc (c *Client) ListWorkflows() ([]Workflow, error)\nfunc (c *Client) StartRun(workflowName string, input string) (*WorkflowRun, error)\nfunc (c *Client) GetRun(id string) (*RunDetailResponse, error)\nfunc (c *Client) ListRuns(status string, limit int) ([]WorkflowRun, error)\nfunc (c *Client) GetEvents(runID string) ([]Event, error)\nfunc (c *Client) CancelRun(id string) error\nfunc (c *Client) Stats() (*StatsResponse, error)\nfunc (c *Client) Health() error\n```\n\nNon-2xx responses are returned as `*APIError{StatusCode int, Message string}`. The client mirrors all server model types locally (`Workflow`, `WorkflowRun`, `ActivityRun`, `Event`, `RunDetailResponse`, `StatsResponse`).\n\n---\n\n## 6. Activity Package: `internal/activity`\n\n### Registry (`registry.go`)\n\n```go\ntype HandlerFunc func(ctx context.Context, input string) (string, error)\n\ntype Registry struct { ... }\n\nfunc NewRegistry() *Registry\nfunc (r *Registry) Register(name string, handler HandlerFunc)\nfunc (r *Registry) Execute(ctx context.Context, name string, input string) (string, error)\n```\n\nThread-safe via `sync.RWMutex`. Returns an error if no handler is registered for the given name.\n\n### WorkerPool (`worker.go`)\n\n```go\ntype ActivityStore interface {\n    ClaimNextActivity() (*model.ActivityRun, error)\n    UpdateActivityRun(ar *model.ActivityRun) error\n    AppendEvent(e *model.Event) error\n}\n\ntype WorkerPool struct { ... }\n\nfunc NewWorkerPool(store ActivityStore, registry *Registry, count int, interval time.Duration) *WorkerPool\nfunc (wp *WorkerPool) Start()   // launches `count` goroutines\nfunc (wp *WorkerPool) Stop()    // signals quit, waits for goroutines\n```\n\nEach worker goroutine in `workerLoop` continuously calls `ClaimNextActivity`, then `executeActivity`. On each execution:\n1. Marks activity `running`, emits `activity_started`\n2. Launches a heartbeat goroutine (ticks every 5s, writes `last_heartbeat` + `activity_heartbeat` event)\n3. Calls `registry.Execute(ctx, ar.ActivityName, ar.Input)` with the configured timeout context\n4. On success: sets `completed`, emits `activity_completed`\n5. On failure with retries remaining: resets to `pending`, emits `activity_retried` or `activity_timed_out`\n6. On failure with retries exhausted: sets `failed`, emits `activity_failed` or `activity_timed_out`\n\n### Built-in Handlers (`builtin.go`)\n\nRegistered by `RegisterBuiltins(r *Registry)`:\n\n| Name | Input | Output | Description |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| `noop` | any | same as input | Pass-through |\n| `sleep` | `{\"duration_ms\": N}` | `{\"slept\": N}` | Sleep for N ms, respects context cancellation |\n| `http-call` | `{\"url\":\"...\", \"method\":\"GET\", \"body\":\"...\"}` | `{\"status\": N, \"body\":\"...\"}` | Makes an HTTP request |\n| `log` | `{\"message\": \"...\"}` | `{\"logged\": true}` | Logs a message via `log.Printf` |\n| `fail` | any | error | Always returns an error (for testing retries) |\n\n---\n\n## 7. Executor Package: `internal/executor`\n\n### `RunStore` Interface\n\n```go\ntype RunStore interface {\n    GetRun(id string) (*model.WorkflowRun, error)\n    UpdateRun(r *model.WorkflowRun) error\n    GetWorkflow(id string) (*model.Workflow, error)\n    CreateActivityRun(ar *model.ActivityRun) error\n    GetActivityRunsByRunID(runID string) ([]model.ActivityRun, error)\n    AppendEvent(e *model.Event) error\n    ListRuns(status string, limit int) ([]model.WorkflowRun, error)\n}\n```\n\n### `Executor` (`executor.go`)\n\n```go\nfunc NewExecutor(store RunStore) *Executor\nfunc (e *Executor) StartRun(runID string) error\nfunc (e *Executor) CancelRun(runID string) error\nfunc (e *Executor) AdvanceRun(runID string) error\n```\n\n`AdvanceRun` is the core state machine:\n- If `currentStep >= len(activities)`: complete the run\n- If no `ActivityRun` exists for `currentStep`: call `scheduleActivity` (creates `ActivityRun` + emits `activity_scheduled`)\n- If current activity is `completed`: increment `CurrentStep`, schedule next activity (or complete run)\n- If current activity is `failed` with retries exhausted: fail the run\n- If current activity is `pending`/`running`: do nothing (wait)\n\nInput expression resolution via `resolveInputExpr`:\n- `\"$.input\"` → workflow run's raw input\n- `\"$.steps[N].output\"` → Nth activity run's output\n- anything else (or empty) → workflow run's raw input\n\n### `Scheduler` (`scheduler.go`)\n\n```go\nfunc NewScheduler(executor *Executor, store RunStore, interval time.Duration) *Scheduler\nfunc (s *Scheduler) Start()   // background goroutine\nfunc (s *Scheduler) Stop()    // closes quit channel\n```\n\nOn every tick (`500ms` by default from `cmd/server/main.go`):\n1. Lists all `pending` runs (up to 100), calls `executor.StartRun` on each\n2. Lists all `running` runs (up to 100), calls `executor.AdvanceRun` on each\n\n---\n\n## 8. Config: `internal/config`\n\n```go\ntype Config struct {\n    Port        string   // default: \"8080\", env: PORT\n    DBPath      string   // default: \"./miniflow.db\", env: DB_PATH\n    WorkerCount int      // default: 4, env: WORKER_COUNT\n}\n\nfunc Load() Config\n```\n\n---\n\n## Server Startup Wiring (`cmd/server/main.go`)\n\n```\nconfig.Load()\n  -> store.NewStore(cfg.DBPath)\n  -> activity.NewRegistry() + RegisterBuiltins()\n  -> activity.NewWorkerPool(store, registry, cfg.WorkerCount, 500ms).Start()\n  -> executor.NewExecutor(store)\n  -> executor.NewScheduler(ex, store, 500ms).Start()\n  -> handler.New(store, ex) -> http.Server on :PORT\n  -> graceful shutdown on SIGINT/SIGTERM\n```\n\nBoth the scheduler and worker pool poll at **500ms intervals**. The scheduler drives the workflow state machine; the worker pool claims and executes individual activities. The `store.Store` satisfies both the `RunStore` and `ActivityStore` interfaces directly."}],"totalDurationMs":81872,"totalTokens":51286,"totalToolUseCount":18,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":7871,"cache_read_input_tokens":39065,"output_tokens":4349,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":7871,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
