{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01Tq8CFv5m5pDQQmWQ63tWKv","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package handler\n     2→\n     3→import \"miniflow/internal/model\"\n     4→\n     5→// CreateWorkflowRequest is the body for POST /api/workflows.\n     6→type CreateWorkflowRequest struct {\n     7→\tName       string                   `json:\"name\"`\n     8→\tDefinition model.WorkflowDefinition `json:\"definition\"`\n     9→}\n    10→\n    11→// StartRunRequest is the body for POST /api/workflows/{name}/run.\n    12→type StartRunRequest struct {\n    13→\tInput string `json:\"input\"`\n    14→}\n    15→\n    16→// RunDetailResponse extends WorkflowRun with activity run details.\n    17→type RunDetailResponse struct {\n    18→\tmodel.WorkflowRun\n    19→\tActivities []model.ActivityRun `json:\"activities\"`\n    20→}\n    21→\n    22→// StatsResponse is the response for GET /api/stats.\n    23→type StatsResponse struct {\n    24→\tCounts map[string]int `json:\"counts\"`\n    25→}\n    26→\n    27→// ErrorResponse is a standard error envelope.\n    28→type ErrorResponse struct {\n    29→\tError string `json:\"error\"`\n    30→}\n    31→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01RYc77eg1Vd2uLiYg8Wm6kb","session_id":"701e3a6a-36af-4762-8d76-051700988d74","uuid":"e90019d1-e76f-40b3-bfd6-689f5d3fef2a"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_013HudKCtvgw8hWmk6ySA1BT","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01NHF3R5g7kdFioUm6bPGqQp","name":"Agent","input":{"description":"Failure & edge case tester","subagent_type":"general-purpose","prompt":"You are the Failure & Edge Case Tester for the miniflow project. You need to create 1 test file in /Users/michaelhabib/dev/teams-sbx/agent-orchestra/examples/miniflow/tests/\n\nThe miniflow project is at /Users/michaelhabib/dev/teams-sbx/agent-orchestra/examples/miniflow/\n\n## Technical Context\n\nminiflow is a workflow execution engine. Tech stack: Go 1.22+, httptest.NewServer, no external test deps.\n\nKey packages:\n- `internal/model` — Workflow, WorkflowRun, ActivityRun, Event types\n- `internal/store` — SQLite persistence (Store struct with NewStore(dsn), all CRUD methods)\n- `internal/activity` — Registry (NewRegistry, Register, Execute), WorkerPool (NewWorkerPool(store, registry, count, interval), Start(), Stop()), RegisterBuiltins()\n- `internal/executor` — Executor (NewExecutor(store), StartRun, CancelRun, AdvanceRun), Scheduler (NewScheduler(ex, store, interval), Start(), Stop())\n- `internal/handler` — handler.New(store, executor) returns http.Handler with chi routing\n- `internal/client` — client.NewClient(baseURL) with methods: RegisterWorkflow, GetWorkflow, ListWorkflows, StartRun, GetRun, ListRuns, GetEvents, CancelRun, Stats, Health\n\nModule name is `miniflow` (in go.mod).\n\nKey types:\n```go\n// model.ActivitySpec\ntype ActivitySpec struct {\n    Name           string `json:\"name\"`\n    Type           string `json:\"type\"`\n    InputExpr      string `json:\"input_expr\"`\n    TimeoutSeconds int    `json:\"timeout_seconds\"`\n    MaxRetries     int    `json:\"max_retries\"`\n}\n\n// model.WorkflowDefinition\ntype WorkflowDefinition struct {\n    Activities []ActivitySpec `json:\"activities\"`\n}\n\n// model.WorkflowRun statuses: \"pending\", \"running\", \"completed\", \"failed\", \"cancelled\"\n// model.ActivityRun statuses: \"pending\", \"running\", \"completed\", \"failed\"\n\n// model.Event types: workflow_started, workflow_completed, workflow_failed, workflow_cancelled,\n//   activity_scheduled, activity_started, activity_completed, activity_failed, activity_retried, activity_timed_out, activity_heartbeat\n```\n\nStore methods: NewStore(dsn), Close(), CreateWorkflow, GetWorkflow, GetWorkflowByName, ListWorkflows, CreateRun, GetRun, ListRuns(status, limit), UpdateRun, CreateActivityRun, GetActivityRun, GetActivityRunsByRunID, UpdateActivityRun, ClaimNextActivity, AppendEvent, ListEvents(runID), Stats\n\nhandler.New(store *store.Store, ex *executor.Executor) http.Handler — routes:\n- POST /api/workflows, GET /api/workflows, GET /api/workflows/{name}\n- POST /api/workflows/{name}/run, GET /api/runs?status=&limit=, GET /api/runs/{id}\n- GET /api/runs/{id}/events, POST /api/runs/{id}/cancel, GET /api/stats, GET /health\n\nClient: client.NewClient(baseURL) \nMethods: RegisterWorkflow(name string, def WorkflowDefinition) (*Workflow, error), StartRun(workflowName, input string) (*WorkflowRun, error), GetRun(id) (*RunDetailResponse, error), ListRuns(status, limit), GetEvents(runID) ([]Event, error), CancelRun(id) error, Stats() (*StatsResponse, error)\n\nClient types:\n```go\ntype ActivitySpec struct { Name, Type, InputExpr string; TimeoutSeconds, MaxRetries int }\ntype WorkflowDefinition struct { Activities []ActivitySpec }\ntype Workflow struct { ID, Name string; Definition WorkflowDefinition; CreatedAt time.Time }\ntype WorkflowRun struct { ID, WorkflowID, Status, Input, Output string; CurrentStep int; StartedAt, CompletedAt *time.Time; CreatedAt time.Time }\ntype ActivityRun struct { ID, WorkflowRunID, ActivityName, Status, Input, Output string; StepIndex, Attempts, MaxRetries, TimeoutSeconds int; ... }\ntype RunDetailResponse struct { WorkflowRun; Activities []ActivityRun }\ntype Event struct { ID int64; WorkflowRunID, ActivityRunID, EventType, Payload string; CreatedAt time.Time }\ntype StatsResponse struct { Counts map[string]int }\ntype APIError struct { StatusCode int; Message string } // implements error\n```\n\nBuilt-in activity types: noop (pass-through), sleep (sleeps duration_ms from input JSON), log (logs message), fail (always errors for retry testing)\n\nWorker pool: activity.NewWorkerPool(store, registry, count, interval) — Start()/Stop()\nScheduler: executor.NewScheduler(ex, store, interval) — Start()/Stop()\nRegisterBuiltins(r *Registry) registers noop, sleep, http-call, log, fail handlers.\n\n## IMPORTANT: This test file shares a package with helpers_test.go\n\nAnother teammate is creating `tests/helpers_test.go` with these helpers you MUST use:\n```go\npackage tests\n\ntype testEnv struct {\n    store      *store.Store\n    handler    http.Handler\n    server     *httptest.Server\n    client     *client.Client\n    executor   *executor.Executor\n    scheduler  *executor.Scheduler\n    workerPool *activity.WorkerPool\n}\n\nfunc newTestEnv(t *testing.T) *testEnv\n// Creates store, executor, handler, httptest server, client. NO workers/scheduler.\n\nfunc newTestEnvWithWorkers(t *testing.T, count int) *testEnv\n// Same + activity registry with builtins, worker pool, scheduler. Starts both.\n\nfunc registerTestWorkflow(t *testing.T, c *client.Client, name string, activities []client.ActivitySpec) *client.Workflow\n// Registers workflow, fatals on error\n\nfunc waitForRunStatus(t *testing.T, c *client.Client, runID string, status string, timeout time.Duration)\n// Polls GetRun every 50ms until status matches or timeout\n\nfunc sampleWorkflow(specs ...client.ActivitySpec) []client.ActivitySpec\n// Returns specs (convenience)\n```\n\n## YOUR TASK: Create tests/failure_test.go\n\nPackage: `package tests`\n\nTests:\n\n1. **TestActivityRetryOnFailure**: Register a workflow with a single \"fail\" activity (type=\"fail\", max_retries=2). Use newTestEnvWithWorkers. StartRun. Wait for status \"failed\" (timeout 5s). GetRun. Verify the activity's Attempts > 1 (retries happened) and activity status is \"failed\". Verify the run status is \"failed\".\n\n2. **TestCancelRunningWorkflow**: Register a workflow with a long sleep activity (type=\"sleep\", input_expr not needed — the sleep handler reads duration_ms from input). Use newTestEnvWithWorkers. StartRun with input `{\"duration_ms\":5000}`. Sleep briefly (200ms) to let it start. CancelRun. Wait a bit. GetRun, verify status=\"cancelled\".\n\n3. **TestCancelPendingRun**: Use newTestEnv (NO workers — run stays pending). Register workflow. StartRun. The run should stay pending. CancelRun. GetRun. Verify status=\"cancelled\".\n\n4. **TestEventHistory**: Use newTestEnvWithWorkers. Register 2-step noop workflow. StartRun. Wait completed. GetEvents. Verify the event types include at minimum: workflow_started, activity_scheduled, activity_started, activity_completed (for first activity), activity_scheduled, activity_started, activity_completed (for second), workflow_completed. Don't check exact order strictly — just verify all expected event types are present with correct counts.\n\n5. **TestConcurrentRuns**: Use newTestEnvWithWorkers(t, 4) for parallelism. Register a 2-step noop workflow. Start 3 runs simultaneously (in a loop). Wait for all 3 to reach \"completed\" (timeout 10s). Verify all 3 have status completed.\n\n6. **TestGetNonexistentRun**: Use newTestEnv. GetRun with a fake UUID. Verify error returned (should be an *client.APIError with StatusCode 404).\n\n## IMPORTANT NOTES\n- File must use `package tests`\n- Read the actual source files before writing tests to understand exact APIs\n- Read the client package (internal/client/client.go) for exact type names\n- Use the helper functions from helpers_test.go (they'll be in the same package)\n- Use short durations for fast tests (50ms polls, 5-10s timeouts)\n- The \"fail\" activity always returns an error — with max_retries=2, the worker will retry up to 2 times before marking failed\n- For TestCancelRunningWorkflow: the executor's CancelRun method handles cancellation. The run may already be \"running\" when you cancel.\n- For APIError checking, use errors.As or type assertion: `var apiErr *client.APIError; errors.As(err, &apiErr)`\n\n## VERIFICATION\nAfter writing the file, run:\n```bash\ncd /Users/michaelhabib/dev/teams-sbx/agent-orchestra/examples/miniflow && go vet ./tests/...\ncd /Users/michaelhabib/dev/teams-sbx/agent-orchestra/examples/miniflow && go test ./tests/... -run 'TestActivity|TestCancel|TestEvent|TestConcurrent|TestGetNon' -v -timeout 30s\n```\n\nFix any compilation errors or test failures. All tests must pass.\n\nNOTE: The helpers_test.go file may not exist yet when you first try to compile. If so, you'll need to create a minimal version or wait. But try writing your file first, then read helpers_test.go if it exists, and verify compilation."},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":270,"cache_read_input_tokens":28157,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":270},"output_tokens":25,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"701e3a6a-36af-4762-8d76-051700988d74","uuid":"fd7da500-ac4f-4f9b-bd73-d265ac813d98"}
