{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01RYc77eg1Vd2uLiYg8Wm6kb","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"All three test files have been created and all tests pass. Here is a summary:\n\n## Files Created\n\n### 1. `/Users/michaelhabib/dev/teams-sbx/agent-orchestra/examples/miniflow/tests/helpers_test.go`\n\nShared test infrastructure providing:\n- **`testEnv` struct** -- holds store, handler, httptest server, client, executor, scheduler, and worker pool references\n- **`newTestEnv(t)`** -- creates a minimal environment (store, executor, handler, httptest server, client) with no workers or scheduler; cleanup closes server and store\n- **`newTestEnvWithWorkers(t, count)`** -- same as above plus activity registry with builtins, worker pool (50ms poll), and scheduler (50ms interval); cleanup stops scheduler and workers\n- **`registerTestWorkflow(t, c, name, activities)`** -- registers a workflow via the client, fatals on error\n- **`waitForRunStatus(t, c, runID, status, timeout)`** -- polls GetRun every 50ms until status matches or timeout\n- **`sampleWorkflow(specs...)`** -- convenience variadic wrapper returning `[]client.ActivitySpec`\n\n### 2. `/Users/michaelhabib/dev/teams-sbx/agent-orchestra/examples/miniflow/tests/workflow_test.go`\n\nSix tests covering workflow lifecycle:\n- **TestRegisterAndListWorkflows** -- registers 2 workflows, verifies ListWorkflows returns both\n- **TestSimpleWorkflowExecution** -- 2-step noop workflow runs to completion, both activities completed\n- **TestWorkflowWithDataPassing** -- verifies `$.input` and `$.steps[0].output` expressions pass data through noop activities\n- **TestMultiStepWorkflow** -- 4-step workflow (noop, sleep, log, noop) all complete successfully\n- **TestRunWithInput** -- verifies custom input is preserved in the run record\n- **TestListRunsFiltered** -- starts 3 runs, verifies filtering by \"completed\" and \"pending\" statuses\n\n### 3. `/Users/michaelhabib/dev/teams-sbx/agent-orchestra/examples/miniflow/tests/client_test.go`\n\nSix tests covering client API:\n- **TestClientRegisterWorkflow** -- verifies returned workflow has correct name and non-empty ID\n- **TestClientStartAndGetRun** -- verifies GetRun returns correct workflow_id and pending/running status\n- **TestClientListRuns** -- starts 3 runs, waits for completion, verifies ListRuns with status filter\n- **TestClientGetEvents** -- verifies event history includes `workflow_started` and `workflow_completed`\n- **TestClientCancelRun** -- cancels a pending run (no workers), verifies status is \"cancelled\"\n- **TestClientStats** -- verifies Stats endpoint returns completed count >= 1\n\n## Verification Results\n\n- `go vet ./tests/...` -- passes cleanly\n- All 6 workflow tests pass (1.7s)\n- All 6 client tests pass (0.9s)"},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: ad83f7f522532e38d (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 53688\ntool_uses: 36\nduration_ms: 153131</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"701e3a6a-36af-4762-8d76-051700988d74","uuid":"9a5e3d8c-35dc-4e58-a63c-f0f831b41a48","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"You are the Workflow Lifecycle Tester for the miniflow project. You need to create 3 test files in /Users/michaelhabib/dev/teams-sbx/agent-orchestra/examples/miniflow/tests/\n\nThe miniflow project is at /Users/michaelhabib/dev/teams-sbx/agent-orchestra/examples/miniflow/\n\n## Technical Context\n\nminiflow is a workflow execution engine. Tech stack: Go 1.22+, httptest.NewServer, no external test deps.\n\nKey packages:\n- `internal/model` — Workflow, WorkflowRun, ActivityRun, Event types\n- `internal/store` — SQLite persistence (Store struct with NewStore(dsn), all CRUD methods)\n- `internal/activity` — Registry (NewRegistry, Register, Execute), WorkerPool (NewWorkerPool(store, registry, count, interval), Start(), Stop()), RegisterBuiltins()\n- `internal/executor` — Executor (NewExecutor(store), StartRun, CancelRun, AdvanceRun), Scheduler (NewScheduler(ex, store, interval), Start(), Stop())\n- `internal/handler` — handler.New(store, executor) returns http.Handler with chi routing\n- `internal/client` — client.NewClient(baseURL) with methods: RegisterWorkflow, GetWorkflow, ListWorkflows, StartRun, GetRun, ListRuns, GetEvents, CancelRun, Stats, Health\n\nModule name is `miniflow` (in go.mod).\n\nKey types:\n```go\n// model.ActivitySpec\ntype ActivitySpec struct {\n    Name           string `json:\"name\"`\n    Type           string `json:\"type\"`\n    InputExpr      string `json:\"input_expr\"`\n    TimeoutSeconds int    `json:\"timeout_seconds\"`\n    MaxRetries     int    `json:\"max_retries\"`\n}\n\n// model.WorkflowDefinition\ntype WorkflowDefinition struct {\n    Activities []ActivitySpec `json:\"activities\"`\n}\n\n// model.Workflow\ntype Workflow struct {\n    ID, Name string; Definition WorkflowDefinition; CreatedAt time.Time\n}\n\n// model.WorkflowRun statuses: \"pending\", \"running\", \"completed\", \"failed\", \"cancelled\"\ntype WorkflowRun struct {\n    ID, WorkflowID, Status, Input, Output string; CurrentStep int\n    StartedAt, CompletedAt *time.Time; CreatedAt time.Time\n}\n\n// model.ActivityRun statuses: \"pending\", \"running\", \"completed\", \"failed\"\ntype ActivityRun struct {\n    ID, WorkflowRunID, ActivityName, Status, Input, Output string\n    StepIndex, Attempts, MaxRetries, TimeoutSeconds int\n    StartedAt, CompletedAt, LastHeartbeat *time.Time; CreatedAt time.Time\n}\n\n// model.Event\ntype Event struct {\n    ID int64; WorkflowRunID, ActivityRunID, EventType, Payload string; CreatedAt time.Time\n}\n```\n\nEvent type constants: workflow_started, workflow_completed, workflow_failed, workflow_cancelled, activity_scheduled, activity_started, activity_completed, activity_failed, activity_retried, activity_timed_out, activity_heartbeat\n\nStore methods: NewStore(dsn), Close(), CreateWorkflow, GetWorkflow, GetWorkflowByName, ListWorkflows, CreateRun, GetRun, ListRuns(status, limit), UpdateRun, CreateActivityRun, GetActivityRun, GetActivityRunsByRunID, UpdateActivityRun, ClaimNextActivity, AppendEvent, ListEvents(runID), Stats\n\nhandler.New(store *store.Store, ex *executor.Executor) http.Handler — routes:\n- POST /api/workflows, GET /api/workflows, GET /api/workflows/{name}\n- POST /api/workflows/{name}/run, GET /api/runs, GET /api/runs/{id}\n- GET /api/runs/{id}/events, POST /api/runs/{id}/cancel, GET /api/stats, GET /health\n\nClient types mirror server types:\n```go\ntype WorkflowDefinition struct { Activities []ActivitySpec }\ntype Workflow struct { ID, Name string; Definition WorkflowDefinition; CreatedAt time.Time }\ntype WorkflowRun struct { ID, WorkflowID, Status, Input, Output string; CurrentStep int; ... }\ntype RunDetailResponse struct { WorkflowRun; Activities []ActivityRun }\ntype StatsResponse struct { Counts map[string]int }\n```\n\nClient methods: RegisterWorkflow(name string, def WorkflowDefinition) (*Workflow, error), GetWorkflow(name), ListWorkflows, StartRun(workflowName, input string) (*WorkflowRun, error), GetRun(id) (*RunDetailResponse, error), ListRuns(status, limit), GetEvents(runID) ([]Event, error), CancelRun(id) error, Stats() (*StatsResponse, error), Health() error\n\nBuilt-in activity types: noop (pass-through), sleep (duration_ms), log (message), fail (always errors)\n\nWorker pool: activity.NewWorkerPool(store, registry, count, interval) — Start()/Stop() — polls ClaimNextActivity, executes activities, handles retries\nScheduler: executor.NewScheduler(ex, store, interval) — Start()/Stop() — polls pending/running runs, calls StartRun/AdvanceRun\n\nRegisterBuiltins(r *Registry) registers noop, sleep, http-call, log, fail handlers.\n\n## YOUR TASKS\n\n### Task 1: Create tests/helpers_test.go\nPackage: `package tests`\n\nCreate shared test infrastructure:\n- `testEnv` struct holding: store *store.Store, handler http.Handler, server *httptest.Server, client *client.Client, executor *executor.Executor, scheduler *executor.Scheduler, workerPool *activity.WorkerPool\n- `newTestEnv(t *testing.T) *testEnv` — creates store (t.TempDir()+\"/test.db\"), executor, handler, httptest server, client pointed at server URL. NO workers/scheduler. t.Cleanup closes everything.\n- `newTestEnvWithWorkers(t *testing.T, count int) *testEnv` — same as above + creates activity registry with builtins, worker pool (count workers, 50ms poll interval), scheduler (50ms interval). Starts both. t.Cleanup stops both.\n- `registerTestWorkflow(t *testing.T, c *client.Client, name string, activities []client.ActivitySpec) *client.Workflow` — registers workflow via client, fatals on error\n- `waitForRunStatus(t *testing.T, c *client.Client, runID string, status string, timeout time.Duration)` — polls GetRun every 50ms until status matches or timeout (t.Fatal on timeout)\n- `sampleWorkflow(specs ...client.ActivitySpec) []client.ActivitySpec` — just returns specs (convenience)\n\nImportant: The test package needs these imports:\n```go\nimport (\n    \"miniflow/internal/store\"\n    \"miniflow/internal/handler\"\n    \"miniflow/internal/executor\"\n    \"miniflow/internal/activity\"\n    \"miniflow/internal/client\"\n    \"net/http/httptest\"\n    \"path/filepath\"\n    \"testing\"\n    \"time\"\n)\n```\n\n### Task 2: Create tests/workflow_test.go\nPackage: `package tests`\n\nTests:\n1. **TestRegisterAndListWorkflows**: Register 2 workflows with different names and activities. ListWorkflows, verify count=2 and both names present.\n\n2. **TestSimpleWorkflowExecution**: Register a 2-step noop workflow (step1-noop, step2-noop). Use newTestEnvWithWorkers. StartRun with `\"{}\"` input. waitForRunStatus \"completed\". GetRun, verify both activities completed.\n\n3. **TestWorkflowWithDataPassing**: Register workflow: step1 is noop with input_expr=\"$.input\", step2 is noop with input_expr=\"$.steps[0].output\". StartRun with `{\"value\":\"hello\"}`. Wait for completed. GetRun. Verify step2's output contains \"hello\" (the noop handler passes through input as output).\n\n4. **TestMultiStepWorkflow**: 4-step workflow: noop→sleep(duration_ms:10)→log(message:\"test\")→noop. Use newTestEnvWithWorkers. StartRun, wait completed. Verify all 4 activities completed.\n\n5. **TestRunWithInput**: Register noop workflow. StartRun with custom input `{\"key\":\"custom_value\"}`. Wait completed. GetRun. Verify the run's Input field contains the custom input.\n\n6. **TestListRunsFiltered**: Register a workflow. Start 3 runs. Wait for all completed. ListRuns with status=\"\" to get all. Also ListRuns with status=\"completed\" and verify count. Try ListRuns with status=\"pending\" and verify 0.\n\n### Task 3: Create tests/client_test.go\nPackage: `package tests`\n\nTests:\n1. **TestClientRegisterWorkflow**: Use newTestEnv (no workers needed). Register a workflow. Verify returned Workflow has correct name and non-empty ID.\n\n2. **TestClientStartAndGetRun**: Register a workflow, start a run. GetRun with returned ID. Verify run details match (workflow_id set, status is pending or running).\n\n3. **TestClientListRuns**: Register a workflow, start 3 runs. Use newTestEnvWithWorkers so they complete. Wait for all 3 to complete. ListRuns with status=\"completed\". Verify count >= 3.\n\n4. **TestClientGetEvents**: Use newTestEnvWithWorkers. Register 1-step noop workflow. StartRun. Wait completed. GetEvents. Verify events include workflow_started and workflow_completed.\n\n5. **TestClientCancelRun**: Use newTestEnv (no workers — run stays pending). Register workflow. StartRun. CancelRun. GetRun. Verify status is cancelled.\n\n6. **TestClientStats**: Use newTestEnvWithWorkers. Register workflow, start a run, wait completed. Stats(). Verify Counts map has \"completed\" >= 1.\n\n## IMPORTANT NOTES\n- All files must use `package tests` \n- Use t.TempDir() for SQLite paths: `filepath.Join(t.TempDir(), \"test.db\")`\n- Use short durations (10-50ms) for polls/sleeps\n- The client package types (client.ActivitySpec, client.WorkflowDefinition, etc.) mirror model types. Check client.go to see exact type names.\n- Start by reading the client package to understand exact type names and method signatures\n- Start by reading all relevant source files before writing tests\n\n## VERIFICATION\nAfter writing all 3 files, run:\n```bash\ncd /Users/michaelhabib/dev/teams-sbx/agent-orchestra/examples/miniflow && go vet ./tests/...\ncd /Users/michaelhabib/dev/teams-sbx/agent-orchestra/examples/miniflow && go test ./tests/... -run 'TestRegister|TestSimple|TestWorkflowWith|TestMulti|TestRunWith|TestListRuns' -v -timeout 30s\ncd /Users/michaelhabib/dev/teams-sbx/agent-orchestra/examples/miniflow && go test ./tests/... -run 'TestClient' -v -timeout 30s\n```\n\nFix any compilation errors or test failures. All tests must pass.","agentId":"ad83f7f522532e38d","content":[{"type":"text","text":"All three test files have been created and all tests pass. Here is a summary:\n\n## Files Created\n\n### 1. `/Users/michaelhabib/dev/teams-sbx/agent-orchestra/examples/miniflow/tests/helpers_test.go`\n\nShared test infrastructure providing:\n- **`testEnv` struct** -- holds store, handler, httptest server, client, executor, scheduler, and worker pool references\n- **`newTestEnv(t)`** -- creates a minimal environment (store, executor, handler, httptest server, client) with no workers or scheduler; cleanup closes server and store\n- **`newTestEnvWithWorkers(t, count)`** -- same as above plus activity registry with builtins, worker pool (50ms poll), and scheduler (50ms interval); cleanup stops scheduler and workers\n- **`registerTestWorkflow(t, c, name, activities)`** -- registers a workflow via the client, fatals on error\n- **`waitForRunStatus(t, c, runID, status, timeout)`** -- polls GetRun every 50ms until status matches or timeout\n- **`sampleWorkflow(specs...)`** -- convenience variadic wrapper returning `[]client.ActivitySpec`\n\n### 2. `/Users/michaelhabib/dev/teams-sbx/agent-orchestra/examples/miniflow/tests/workflow_test.go`\n\nSix tests covering workflow lifecycle:\n- **TestRegisterAndListWorkflows** -- registers 2 workflows, verifies ListWorkflows returns both\n- **TestSimpleWorkflowExecution** -- 2-step noop workflow runs to completion, both activities completed\n- **TestWorkflowWithDataPassing** -- verifies `$.input` and `$.steps[0].output` expressions pass data through noop activities\n- **TestMultiStepWorkflow** -- 4-step workflow (noop, sleep, log, noop) all complete successfully\n- **TestRunWithInput** -- verifies custom input is preserved in the run record\n- **TestListRunsFiltered** -- starts 3 runs, verifies filtering by \"completed\" and \"pending\" statuses\n\n### 3. `/Users/michaelhabib/dev/teams-sbx/agent-orchestra/examples/miniflow/tests/client_test.go`\n\nSix tests covering client API:\n- **TestClientRegisterWorkflow** -- verifies returned workflow has correct name and non-empty ID\n- **TestClientStartAndGetRun** -- verifies GetRun returns correct workflow_id and pending/running status\n- **TestClientListRuns** -- starts 3 runs, waits for completion, verifies ListRuns with status filter\n- **TestClientGetEvents** -- verifies event history includes `workflow_started` and `workflow_completed`\n- **TestClientCancelRun** -- cancels a pending run (no workers), verifies status is \"cancelled\"\n- **TestClientStats** -- verifies Stats endpoint returns completed count >= 1\n\n## Verification Results\n\n- `go vet ./tests/...` -- passes cleanly\n- All 6 workflow tests pass (1.7s)\n- All 6 client tests pass (0.9s)"}],"totalDurationMs":153131,"totalTokens":53688,"totalToolUseCount":36,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":273,"cache_read_input_tokens":52682,"output_tokens":732,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":273,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01HibZzCNxv3j4gynBJQouLV","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01DvkdHojXEgV2nniRAjmQEL","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/Users/michaelhabib/dev/teams-sbx/agent-orchestra/examples/miniflow/tests/failure_test.go","content":"package tests\n\nimport (\n\t\"errors\"\n\t\"testing\"\n\t\"time\"\n\n\t\"miniflow/internal/client\"\n)\n\nfunc TestActivityRetryOnFailure(t *testing.T) {\n\tenv := newTestEnvWithWorkers(t, 2)\n\n\tregisterTestWorkflow(t, env.client, \"fail-workflow\", sampleWorkflow(\n\t\tclient.ActivitySpec{\n\t\t\tName:       \"always-fail\",\n\t\t\tType:       \"fail\",\n\t\t\tMaxRetries: 2,\n\t\t},\n\t))\n\n\trun, err := env.client.StartRun(\"fail-workflow\", \"{}\")\n\tif err != nil {\n\t\tt.Fatalf(\"StartRun: %v\", err)\n\t}\n\n\twaitForRunStatus(t, env.client, run.ID, \"failed\", 10*time.Second)\n\n\tdetail, err := env.client.GetRun(run.ID)\n\tif err != nil {\n\t\tt.Fatalf(\"GetRun: %v\", err)\n\t}\n\n\tif detail.Status != \"failed\" {\n\t\tt.Errorf(\"expected run status 'failed', got %q\", detail.Status)\n\t}\n\n\tif len(detail.Activities) == 0 {\n\t\tt.Fatal(\"expected at least one activity run\")\n\t}\n\n\tact := detail.Activities[0]\n\tif act.Status != \"failed\" {\n\t\tt.Errorf(\"expected activity status 'failed', got %q\", act.Status)\n\t}\n\tif act.Attempts <= 1 {\n\t\tt.Errorf(\"expected Attempts > 1 (retries happened), got %d\", act.Attempts)\n\t}\n}\n\nfunc TestCancelRunningWorkflow(t *testing.T) {\n\tenv := newTestEnvWithWorkers(t, 2)\n\n\tregisterTestWorkflow(t, env.client, \"sleep-workflow\", sampleWorkflow(\n\t\tclient.ActivitySpec{\n\t\t\tName: \"long-sleep\",\n\t\t\tType: \"sleep\",\n\t\t},\n\t))\n\n\trun, err := env.client.StartRun(\"sleep-workflow\", `{\"duration_ms\":5000}`)\n\tif err != nil {\n\t\tt.Fatalf(\"StartRun: %v\", err)\n\t}\n\n\t// Give the scheduler time to pick up and start the run.\n\ttime.Sleep(200 * time.Millisecond)\n\n\tif err := env.client.CancelRun(run.ID); err != nil {\n\t\tt.Fatalf(\"CancelRun: %v\", err)\n\t}\n\n\t// Allow a brief moment for the cancellation to propagate.\n\ttime.Sleep(100 * time.Millisecond)\n\n\tdetail, err := env.client.GetRun(run.ID)\n\tif err != nil {\n\t\tt.Fatalf(\"GetRun: %v\", err)\n\t}\n\n\tif detail.Status != \"cancelled\" {\n\t\tt.Errorf(\"expected run status 'cancelled', got %q\", detail.Status)\n\t}\n}\n\nfunc TestCancelPendingRun(t *testing.T) {\n\tenv := newTestEnv(t) // No workers — run stays pending.\n\n\tregisterTestWorkflow(t, env.client, \"noop-workflow\", sampleWorkflow(\n\t\tclient.ActivitySpec{\n\t\t\tName: \"step1\",\n\t\t\tType: \"noop\",\n\t\t},\n\t))\n\n\trun, err := env.client.StartRun(\"noop-workflow\", \"{}\")\n\tif err != nil {\n\t\tt.Fatalf(\"StartRun: %v\", err)\n\t}\n\n\t// Verify run is still pending (no workers to pick it up).\n\tdetail, err := env.client.GetRun(run.ID)\n\tif err != nil {\n\t\tt.Fatalf(\"GetRun: %v\", err)\n\t}\n\tif detail.Status != \"pending\" {\n\t\tt.Fatalf(\"expected run to be 'pending' without workers, got %q\", detail.Status)\n\t}\n\n\tif err := env.client.CancelRun(run.ID); err != nil {\n\t\tt.Fatalf(\"CancelRun: %v\", err)\n\t}\n\n\tdetail, err = env.client.GetRun(run.ID)\n\tif err != nil {\n\t\tt.Fatalf(\"GetRun after cancel: %v\", err)\n\t}\n\tif detail.Status != \"cancelled\" {\n\t\tt.Errorf(\"expected run status 'cancelled', got %q\", detail.Status)\n\t}\n}\n\nfunc TestEventHistory(t *testing.T) {\n\tenv := newTestEnvWithWorkers(t, 2)\n\n\tregisterTestWorkflow(t, env.client, \"two-noop\", sampleWorkflow(\n\t\tclient.ActivitySpec{Name: \"step1\", Type: \"noop\"},\n\t\tclient.ActivitySpec{Name: \"step2\", Type: \"noop\"},\n\t))\n\n\trun, err := env.client.StartRun(\"two-noop\", `{\"msg\":\"hello\"}`)\n\tif err != nil {\n\t\tt.Fatalf(\"StartRun: %v\", err)\n\t}\n\n\twaitForRunStatus(t, env.client, run.ID, \"completed\", 10*time.Second)\n\n\tevents, err := env.client.GetEvents(run.ID)\n\tif err != nil {\n\t\tt.Fatalf(\"GetEvents: %v\", err)\n\t}\n\n\t// Count event types.\n\tcounts := make(map[string]int)\n\tfor _, ev := range events {\n\t\tcounts[ev.EventType]++\n\t}\n\n\t// Verify expected event types and minimum counts.\n\texpected := map[string]int{\n\t\t\"workflow_started\":   1,\n\t\t\"workflow_completed\": 1,\n\t\t\"activity_scheduled\": 2, // one per activity\n\t\t\"activity_started\":   2,\n\t\t\"activity_completed\": 2,\n\t}\n\n\tfor evType, minCount := range expected {\n\t\tif counts[evType] < minCount {\n\t\t\tt.Errorf(\"expected at least %d %q events, got %d\", minCount, evType, counts[evType])\n\t\t}\n\t}\n}\n\nfunc TestConcurrentRuns(t *testing.T) {\n\tenv := newTestEnvWithWorkers(t, 4)\n\n\tregisterTestWorkflow(t, env.client, \"concurrent-noop\", sampleWorkflow(\n\t\tclient.ActivitySpec{Name: \"step1\", Type: \"noop\"},\n\t\tclient.ActivitySpec{Name: \"step2\", Type: \"noop\"},\n\t))\n\n\tconst numRuns = 3\n\trunIDs := make([]string, numRuns)\n\tfor i := 0; i < numRuns; i++ {\n\t\trun, err := env.client.StartRun(\"concurrent-noop\", `{\"run_index\":`+string(rune('0'+i))+`}`)\n\t\tif err != nil {\n\t\t\tt.Fatalf(\"StartRun[%d]: %v\", i, err)\n\t\t}\n\t\trunIDs[i] = run.ID\n\t}\n\n\t// Wait for all runs to complete.\n\tfor i, id := range runIDs {\n\t\twaitForRunStatus(t, env.client, id, \"completed\", 10*time.Second)\n\n\t\tdetail, err := env.client.GetRun(id)\n\t\tif err != nil {\n\t\t\tt.Fatalf(\"GetRun[%d]: %v\", i, err)\n\t\t}\n\t\tif detail.Status != \"completed\" {\n\t\t\tt.Errorf(\"run[%d] expected status 'completed', got %q\", i, detail.Status)\n\t\t}\n\t}\n}\n\nfunc TestGetNonexistentRun(t *testing.T) {\n\tenv := newTestEnv(t)\n\n\t_, err := env.client.GetRun(\"00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000\")\n\tif err == nil {\n\t\tt.Fatal(\"expected error for nonexistent run, got nil\")\n\t}\n\n\tvar apiErr *client.APIError\n\tif !errors.As(err, &apiErr) {\n\t\tt.Fatalf(\"expected *client.APIError, got %T: %v\", err, err)\n\t}\n\tif apiErr.StatusCode != 404 {\n\t\tt.Errorf(\"expected status code 404, got %d\", apiErr.StatusCode)\n\t}\n}\n"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1699,"cache_read_input_tokens":46592,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1699},"output_tokens":4,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01NHF3R5g7kdFioUm6bPGqQp","session_id":"701e3a6a-36af-4762-8d76-051700988d74","uuid":"9c573b05-7565-4272-b1de-ff1c6e33fd9c"}
